You can use a ripe avocado in many different ways. A good method of telling if an avocado is ripe is to gently squeeze the fruit; if it yields to pressure and doesn’t feel too hard or too soft it is probably ripe and ready to use. Here are 5 different methods for using a ripe avocado: 
1. Mashing and using it as butter with salt and pepper to make a vegan popcorn alternative;
2. Mashing and spreading it as face mask to aid moisturizing dry skin;
3. Using the flesh of the avocado as an enzyme in a recipe like: seven layer dip, Creamy Zucchini Bread or Creamy Tomato Soup;
4. Mixing with yogurt and/or eggs to add a creamy aspect to omelets and salads;
5. Adding finely diced pieces to a salad, or use sliced avocado as a sandwich cut for a BLT

